&lt;p&gt;Blacklane works with thousands of professional chauffeurs around the globe. They are the face of Blacklane and play a key role in delivering our quality standards every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the KSA Operations team, you will support and motivate our chauffeur partners to deliver a consistently safe, reliable, and elevated guest experience. You will be a key pillar of Blacklane’s training and quality standards in KSA, helping maintain and continuously improve the quality of our chauffeur services through data-driven insights, effective training programs, and a strong culture of excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are detail-oriented and care deeply about luxury, sustainability, and exceptional quality, we would love to speak with you. You will be joining an international team that is excited to welcome you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;col-md-6 pull-left&quot;&gt;YOUR CHALLENGE:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and lead Blacklane’s chauffeur training academy and programs in KSA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and expand theoretical and practical courses across all segments of chauffeur training, and manage our Learning Management Systems in both English and Arabic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with our partners to understand their customization requirements and train chauffeurs accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on the ground with chauffeurs to provide on-the-job training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data to identify areas for improvement in chauffeur performance and quality, and provide insights for new training materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage our auditing process, quality assurance frameworks, and conduct spot checks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the quality of our partners by analyzing data, setting clear expectations, and providing frameworks for other operations teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver theoretical and practical sessions covering the key competency areas identified in the core chauffeur training modules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote a culture of teamwork, sustainability, stability, respect, and tolerance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share feedback and continuously improve the effectiveness of course materials with your Team Lead and Head of Operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;col-md-6 pull-left&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;border&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;ABOUT YOU:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of relevant work experience in a business environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A clear commitment to quality, professionalism, and delivering high-quality services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An in-depth understanding of luxury service elements and the ability to ensure guest satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong interest in operational execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience setting up and implementing quality and training programs within luxury industries, with a track record of improving performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skill in data analysis, including gathering, analyzing, and drawing meaningful conclusions to generate insights and improve existing approaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to motivate teams to improve each day and build a sense of pride in chauffeuring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational and communication skills, with the ability to multitask and prioritize effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills and cultural sensitivity, coupled with effective communication and presentation abilities for diverse groups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership qualities and the ability to lead and inspire teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
