&lt;li class=&quot;col-md-6 pull-left&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ambiguity:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;You are not afraid of working with ambiguous requirements and turning them into concrete deliverables. You are comfortable making trade-off decisions and understand that “perfect is the enemy of done”.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Evolution:&lt;/strong&gt; You act as a coach and a talent magnet. You will be responsible for the growth, performance, and structure of the Platform unit, ensuring we have a vocal, collaborative, and high-performing culture through continuous learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Raise the Bar: &lt;/strong&gt;You drive Platform excellence, may it be developer experience, infrastructure or SRE. Communication: You communicate regularly with the other Engineering Managers, manage their expectations and hold them accountable for delivery dependencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Profile: The Practical Strategist&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a leader who builds high-performing teams. Whether your background is in Platform, Backend, or Data Engineering, you are someone who thrives on solving &quot;the hard stuff&quot;, is motivated to educate themself and never leaves a job 80% finished. This is your chance to shape a Platform Domain from the ground up.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High Agency:&lt;/strong&gt; You don&#39;t wait for permission to fix a glaring problem. You build the business case, get the buy-in, and get it done.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execution-Focused:&lt;/strong&gt; You have a track record of taking complex initiatives across the finish line. You understand that &quot;80% done&quot; is often where the most critical technical debt lives, and you have the discipline to drive projects to true 100% completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong opinions, weakly held:&lt;/strong&gt; You have strong opinions on how things should be done, but you are Okay to disagree and commit in order to move forward.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
